news.title: Cera Sanitaryware's net profit up 31.91% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Cera Sanitaryware's net consolidated income stood at Rs 471.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 20.06 per cent from Rs 392.35 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 23.74% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net consolidated income stood at Rs 294.80 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 36.39 per cent from Rs 216.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net profit up 44.54% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Godrej Properties' net consolidated income stood at Rs 404.58 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 13.35 per cent from Rs 466.91 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: More affordable housing expected in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The state government has estimated that within the next five years rapid urbanization in Uttar Pradesh will lead to demand for 64 lakh new housing units.

news.title: Bombay HC unhappy as civic bodies raze only 227 of 4,668 illegal structures in six months
news.para: A division bench comprising justices Atul Chandurkar and Vrushali Joshi also asked the police to provide security to teams of NMC, NIT and NMRDA during anti-encroachment drives in the city.

news.title: Enforcement wing of Jaipur development body razes illegal colony in PRN
news.para: Officials said despite several notices in the past and a written affidavit from the owner of the plot promising to remove all illegal commercial activities, the owner continued to build unsanctioned shops and was giving them on rent.

news.title: Residential houses, PG stays swelling on OMR in Tamil Nadu
news.para: With many companies asking staff to return to work, traffic on the stretch has increased. So has the demand for houses, especially rental and paying guest accommodation.

news.title: Delhi court denies bail to Ajay Nawandar in DHFL bank fraud case
news.para: ​Special Judge Ashwani Kumar Sarpal noted that the accused had manipulated the medical record in procuring interim bail in the case, and said that the chances of tampering of evidence and influencing public witnesses by the accused were greater.

news.title: Flats for sale: Nine cheated of Rs 7 lakh with sham ads in Noida
news.para: Detailing the modus operandi of the gang, Ashutosh Dwivedi, additional deputy commissioner of police, Noida, said that the gang would post fake property ads with the gang's mobile number on popular housing websites.

news.title: Ex-Unitech promoters in SC seeks hearing on bail pleas in financial fraud case
news.para: During the hearing, the top court asked the Noida authority to process the layout and building plans of Unitech Group, without asking for the upfront payment of dues.

news.title: Chennai development body minister holds meeting with builders' association
news.para: During the meeting, BAI representatives highlighted some of the demands and also submitted a list of issues faced by the construction industry to the minister.

news.title: Headless RERA in Telangana worries realtors as projects come to halt
news.para: According to official data, the last project approved for registration was on January 4 before Somesh Kumar was sent back to Andhra Pradesh as per the Telangana high court's order.

news.title: Bolstered infrastructure investment-a catalyst for a $5 trillion economy: Niranjan Hiranandani
news.para: Last-mile connectivity with multi-transit corridors and infrastructure investments will open up vast hinterlands for future real estate developments.

news.title: UK house prices fall more than expected in January 2023: Nationwide
news.para: January's decline in house prices was the fourth drop in a row - the longest unbroken run of declines since 2009 - and the fall was twice the size expected in a Reuters poll of economists, adding to signs that the market is slowing rapidly.

news.title: Real Estate Budget 2023: Double non-taxation on REITs finally addressed
news.para: From April 1, 2024 all distribution by a REIT/InvIT representing repayment of debt is taxable as "other income" in the hands of the unit holders.
